Kicktoo is meant to automate the manual steps required to build a working Portage based distro.

WARNING: You should NOT run it on anything else than a LiveCD.

To use Kicktoo:

1) Download a Linux LiveCD, preferably SysrescueCD or Ubuntu

2) Boot the LiveCD

3) Setup network connectivity

4) Download Kicktoo from github.com
   # git clone git://github.com/r1k0/kicktoo.git

5) Customize one of the default profiles
   # vim kicktoo/profiles/gentoo/gentoo.profile

6) Run Kicktoo
   # ./kicktoo -v profiles/gentoo/gentoo.profile

7) Reboot

